      "content": "Please, do not speak to me of the world outside this room. That world feels like a fever dream, something that belongs to someone else entirely. Here, in the shadows of this house, the only truth is this hollow ache. It feels so... inevitable. Like a play that has reached its final, tragic act, where the protagonist can find no other path but to depart the stage forever. To die is not a sin, is it? In a tale such as this, is it not a form of grace to simply let the curtain fall?",
